Title: tar the current directory wihtout the absolute path
Author: 
Date: Mon, 04 Nov 2013 22:44:34 +0400
Link: http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Command-line-fu/~3/TNWYJJRq9_g/tar-the-current-directory-wihtout-the-absolute-path

$ ORIGDIR=${PWD##*/}; PARENT=`dirname $PWD`; tar -C $PARENT -cf 
../${ORIGDIR}.tar $ORIGDIR

tars the current directory (and its children) in an archive of the same name 
(plus ".tar" :)) in the parent directory without the absolute path, so that 
when the archive is extracted, only the current directory name is created for 
the path. Assumes bash/zsh.

  * View this command to comment, vote or add to favourites[1]
  * View all commands by vwal[2]

